(6, 1, '2017-01-16 19:43:09', '2017-01-16 19:43:09', 'Are you in the market for a new home in Harford County? One of the biggest considerations when deciding to build a new home is budget. Gemcraft Homes builds homes suitable for every budget, whether you want to be in one of our communities or want to build on a lot of your own.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-15" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/contact-card-bg-3-228x300.jpg" alt="" width="228" height="300" />\r\n\r\nWe currently build in nine communities in sought-after locations in Harford County, and have several floorplans to choose from in each location, ensuring you find something to fit your needs. Homes in Abingdon Manor in Abingdon, MD, start at $291,990 with seven affordable floor plans to choose from. Winter’s Run in Bel Air, MD, offers executive home sites on a private golf course with fairway and greens views starting at $655,990. All of our other communities fall in between, with a variety of locations and plans to fit your needs. While we love the communities we build in, we understand that these may not offer the ideal location that you’re looking for. Gemcraft Custom Select Properties offers the opportunity to build your home on any one of hundreds of available properties throughout central Maryland. Our home site specialist can assist you in finding the ideal home site in your desired location, or we can guide you through the process of building a new home on land that you already own. Choose from any of our 55 floor plans, from 3 bed, 2 bath homes around 2,000 square feet to more extravagant homes with 4 beds, 3 baths up to 5,500 square feet, and everything in between. Many of our homes are customizable with several options to choose from, like a finished lower level, sunroom or luxurious master super bath, to get you all of the space, square footage, and amenities you’re looking for.', 'What Does it Costto Build a NewHome in Harford County?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-does-it-costto-build-a-newhome-in-harford-county', '', '', '2017-01-23 17:12:37', '2017-01-23 17:12:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=6', 0, 'post', '', 0),
